h salt and pepper."},{"content":"Lay 4 sheets of aluminium foil down onto work surface, then line aluminium foil pieces with small pieces of baking paper."},{"content":"Remove plastic wrap from turkey breast steaks and lay 1 turkey steak into the center of each piece of baking paper. Spread reserved stuffing mixture evenly over each steak, then roll steak up."},{"content":"Wrap rolled turkey steaks tightly in the baking paper and aluminium foil, twisting the ends to form a firm sausage shape. Place 2 turkey roulades into Varoma dish and 2 turkey roulades onto Varoma tray."},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position and steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Swap the turkey rolls in the Varoma dish and tray to ensure even cooking, then secure Varoma lid and steam <b>8-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, or until turkey is cooked."},{"content":"Remove turkey roulades from Varoma and set aside to rest for 5 minutes, then unwrap from aluminium foil and baking paper before placing into refrigerator to cool completely (approx. 30 minutes). Once cooled, slice turkey roulades and place onto a platter to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For added colour, you may like to brown your turkey roulade in a hot frying pan just before serving.","Try using the <em>Prune and orange stuffing<\/em>, <em>Apricot stuffing<\/em> or <em>Cranberry bacon stuffing<\/em> in this recipe instead.","Substitute the turkey breast steaks in this recipe with chicken breast fillets for a different flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","4 portions"]}